          "date": "2019-05-27 18:44:41.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-11297 lnet: MR Routing Feature",
        "message": "LU-11297 lnet: MR Routing Feature\n\nThis is a merge commit from the multi-rail branch. It brings in\nthe MR Routing feature. This feature aligns the LNET Multi-Rail\nbehavior with routing. A gateway now is viewed as a Multi-Rail\ncapable node. When a route is added only one entry per gateway\ncan be used. That route entry should use the primary-nid of the\ngateway. The multi-rail selection algorithm is then run when\nsending to the gateway to select the best interface to send to.\n\nFurthermore the gateway aliveness is now kept via the health\nmechanism. And the gateway pinger now uses discovery instead of\nmaintaining its own pinger handler.\n\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <ashehata@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I25fdc493bf223cece8ebb2c139b9e0d41363832a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
